Please give me that.

1635
01:06:17,138 --> 01:06:19,107
There were postcards like this.

1636
01:06:19,108 --> 01:06:20,548
- Postcards.
- Yes.

1637
01:06:20,608 --> 01:06:23,247
- The small postcards, right?
- Yes.

1638
01:06:23,248 --> 01:06:24,347
Of this size. A single postcard.

1639
01:06:24,348 --> 01:06:25,987
- Right. Postcards.
- Right.

1640
01:06:25,988 --> 01:06:27,788
- Postcards...
- We sent those.

1641
01:06:28,088 --> 01:06:29,958
were the number one measure of popularity.

1642
01:06:30,718 --> 01:06:33,258
Contribution came 2nd or 3rd.

1643
01:06:33,528 --> 01:06:35,858
Contribution came after that.

1644
01:06:35,958 --> 01:06:36,958
You received many postcards.

1645
01:06:36,959 --> 01:06:38,657
Let me tell you.

1646
01:06:38,658 --> 01:06:41,368
It wasn't just more than the other singers.

1647
01:06:41,798 --> 01:06:44,038
There was a huge difference in the number of postcards.

1648
01:06:44,368 --> 01:06:46,137
- The number.
- We wrote the postcards.

1649
01:06:46,138 --> 01:06:47,337
I stayed up all night writing postcards...

1650
01:06:47,338 --> 01:06:48,537
- and sending them.
- That's right.

1651
01:06:48,538 --> 01:06:50,307
That's why...

1652
01:06:50,308 --> 01:06:52,647
I couldn't have gotten that award...

1653
01:06:52,648 --> 01:06:54,648
- in terms of the contribution.
- In 1971.

1654
01:06:54,748 --> 01:06:56,778
But I got the award,

1655
01:06:56,978 --> 01:06:58,948
- and everyone was shocked.
