1777
01:11:42,628 --> 01:11:45,337
opposition paper back then.

1778
01:11:45,338 --> 01:11:46,567
(His father was the head of The Mokpo Daily.)

1779
01:11:46,568 --> 01:11:49,537
My homeroom teacher was my tutor when I was in elementary school.

1780
01:11:49,538 --> 01:11:50,937
Then...

1781
01:11:50,938 --> 01:11:52,277
- He was a crown prince.
- I'm sorry.

1782
01:11:52,278 --> 01:11:53,777
Earlier, you said...

1783
01:11:53,778 --> 01:11:55,107
you had listened to music on vinyl records at home.

1784
01:11:55,108 --> 01:11:56,647
- Yes.
- Having a turntable at home...

1785
01:11:56,648 --> 01:11:57,817
was uncommon back then.

1786
01:11:57,818 --> 01:11:59,247
- Even in Seoul, - It was rare.

1787
01:11:59,248 --> 01:12:01,848
not many people had televisions at home.

1788
01:12:02,118 --> 01:12:04,518
Paul Anka was a famous singer at that time.

1789
01:12:05,018 --> 01:12:06,757
There's a song of his...

1790
01:12:06,758 --> 01:12:08,857
that I can never forget.

1791
01:12:08,858 --> 01:12:09,858
(A song that made young Nam Jin's heart flutter)

1792
01:12:09,859 --> 01:12:12,297
It's "Crazy Love."

1793
01:12:12,298 --> 01:12:13,828
- "Crazy Love?"
- "Crazy Love."

1794
01:12:14,028 --> 01:12:16,537
(Crazy)

1795
01:12:16,538 --> 01:12:17,538
(Love)

1796
01:12:17,539 --> 01:12:18,568
It goes like this.

1797
01:12:18,738 --> 01:12:23,508
("Crazy Love" by Paul Anka)

1798
01:12:23,778 --> 01:12:27,648
(He has a good memory!)

1799
01:12:28,008 --> 01:12:29,748
The song reminds me of my father.

1800
01:12:30,018 --> 01:12:33,048
It was when I was in my 10th or 11th grade.

1801
01:12:33,848 --> 01:12:34,848
It was in the 1950s.

1802
01:12:35,018 --> 01:12:36,587
We lived in a two-story house.

1803
01:12:36,588 --> 01:12:37,988
My room was upstairs on the second floor,

1804
01:12:38,688 --> 01:12:40,988
and my father's room was downstairs.

1805
01:12:42,158 --> 01:12:45,158
If I shouted from the 2nd floor, you could hear it on the 1st floor.

1806
01:12:45,358 --> 01:12:47,528
When I sang, I sang very loudly.

1807
01:12:48,268 --> 01:12:50,997
(His father heard him sing "Crazy Love.")

1808
01:12:50,998 --> 01:12:52,907
So my father's comment about my song was funny.

1809
01:12:52,908 --> 01:12:53,908
I see.

1810
01:12:53,968 --> 01:12:54,968
Then he called out my mother.

1811
01:12:55,438 --> 01:12:56,537
"Hey."

1812
01:12:56,538 --> 01:12:58,107
(His father called out his mother in a rush.)

1813
01:12:58,108 --> 01:12:59,338
He called her out.

1814
01:13:00,308 --> 01:13:01,448
He was like, "This is bad."

1815
01:13:02,348 --> 01:13:06,017
He has never heard a song like that.

1816
01:13:06,018 --> 01:13:07,287
(His father was born during the reign of King Gojong of Joseon.)

1817
01:13:07,288 --> 01:13:09,048
He told my mother...

1818
01:13:09,718 --> 01:13:12,588
to take me to the hospital right away.

1819
01:13:13,058 --> 01:13:15,687
(His father was shocked by Western culture.)

1820
01:13:15,688 --> 01:13:16,697
Something like that happened once.

1821
01:13:16,698 --> 01:13:19,097
I guess your father...

1822
01:13:19,098 --> 01:13:20,627
didn't scold you...

1823
01:13:20,628 --> 01:13:21,798
for singing at home.

1824
01:13:21,968 --> 01:13:24,167
He didn't scold me.

1825
01:13:24,168 --> 01:13:26,537
He just thought I was just singing for fun.

1826
01:13:26,538 --> 01:13:29,237
He didn't think I'd become a singer.

1827
01:13:29,238 --> 01:13:31,937
He was the son of a wealthy father,

1828
01:13:31,938 --> 01:13:33,047
born when his father was 50 after having 6 daughters.

1829
01:13:33,048 --> 01:13:34,147
It's a completely different story.

1830
01:13:34,148 --> 01:13:36,178
How would I know? My family wasn't rich.

1831
01:13:40,448 --> 01:13:43,518
Why did he send his precious son to the Vietnam War then?

1832
01:13:45,918 --> 01:13:47,528
It was after he died.

1833
01:13:48,528 --> 01:13:50,157
(Flustered)

1834
01:13:50,158 --> 01:13:51,258
I'm sorry.

1835
01:13:53,298 --> 01:13:54,597
(Laughing)

1836
01:13:54,598 --> 01:13:57,237
If he had been alive,

1837
01:13:57,238 --> 01:13:58,768
he would've never sent you.

1838
01:13:58,998 --> 01:14:00,767
- Right.
- There was no choice.

1839
01:14:00,768 --> 01:14:02,368
The government sent soldiers. It was unavoidable.

1840
01:14:05,808 --> 01:14:09,618
There's a movie about the time when you were young.

1841
01:14:09,678 --> 01:14:10,917
- Right.
- "Ode to My Father."

1842
01:14:10,918 --> 01:14:15,948
(It's a movie set during the Vietnam War.)

1843
01:14:16,418 --> 01:14:18,957
(U-Know played My Star.)

1844
01:14:18,958 --> 01:14:20,587
What are you doing? We don't have time.

1845
01:14:20,588 --> 01:14:22,027
You're driving me nuts.

1846
01:14:22,028 --> 01:14:23,198
Excuse me.

1847
01:14:23,758 --> 01:14:25,828
(Are you Nam Jin?)

1848
01:14:26,298 --> 01:14:27,367
(We'd love to hear the behind-the-scenes story of a movie...)

1849
01:14:27,368 --> 01:14:28,397
(that attracted 10 million viewers.)

1850
01:14:28,398 --> 01:14:30,238
- I asked the director...
- Yes.

1851
01:14:31,268 --> 01:14:33,307
why he cast a singer to play me.

1852
01:14:33,308 --> 01:14:35,267
He said it was because he was from Jeolla Province.

1853
01:14:35,268 --> 01:14:37,207
I said it was a good choice...

1854
01:14:37,208 --> 01:14:38,778
to cast someone who could speak the dialect.

1855
01:14:39,208 --> 01:14:40,747
The same goes for me.

1856
01:14:40,748 --> 01:14:43,277
Unless I play someone from Jeolla Province...

1857
01:14:43,278 --> 01:14:44,377
If I try to speak with a Seoul accent,

1858
01:14:44,378 --> 01:14:45,618
it's obvious I'm not from Seoul.

1859
01:14:47,488 --> 01:14:48,947
(It's been 60 years since he debuted,)

1860
01:14:48,948 --> 01:14:50,417
(but he still can't speak with a Seoul accent.)

1861
01:14:50,418 --> 01:14:52,687
Have you never even had a phone call with U-Know?

1862
01:14:52,688 --> 01:14:55,427
I don't think so. Maybe I've seen him once.

1863
01:14:55,428 --> 01:14:57,827
Do you mind if I call him?

1864
01:14:57,828 --> 01:14:58,858
I don't.

1865
01:15:02,068 --> 01:15:04,838
- Hello.
- U-Know, what are you doing?

1866
01:15:05,298 --> 01:15:07,967
I'm at a family year-end gathering.

1867
01:15:07,968 --> 01:15:09,737
- A family year-end gathering?
- He has a nice voice.

1868
01:15:09,738 --> 01:15:11,208
You're busy.

1869
01:15:12,438 --> 01:15:13,577
I should do my best.

1870
01:15:13,578 --> 01:15:15,307
(He does his best even at a family gathering.)

1871
01:15:15,308 --> 01:15:17,348
Are you not doing a challenge with your family?

1872
01:15:18,778 --> 01:15:20,087
- U-Know.
- Yes.

1873
01:15:20,088 --> 01:15:23,588
Nam Jin is with us today for a shoot.

1874
01:15:23,658 --> 01:15:25,117
Nam Jin.

1875
01:15:25,118 --> 01:15:26,728
U-Know, how have you been?

1876
01:15:27,058 --> 01:15:29,857
Oh, my gosh. How have you been?

1877
01:15:29,858 --> 01:15:31,128
Is everything all right?

1878
01:15:31,298 --> 01:15:33,527
- Everything is good.
- Okay.

1879
01:15:33,528 --> 01:15:34,528
(They immediately start speaking in their hometown accent.)

1880
01:15:35,728 --> 01:15:37,297
It's been a long time since I saw you.

1881
01:15:37,298 --> 01:15:40,467
But I always remember...

1882
01:15:40,468 --> 01:15:42,007
how you portrayed me in the movie.

1883
01:15:42,008 --> 01:15:44,137
- It was...
- You flatter me.

1884
01:15:44,138 --> 01:15:47,047
It was an honor to act out your life.

1885
01:15:47,048 --> 01:15:51,117
No. I hope you achieve...

1886
01:15:51,118 --> 01:15:53,017
more success than I have.

1887
01:15:53,018 --> 01:15:54,347
- Thank you.
- Okay?

1888
01:15:54,348 --> 01:15:55,448
Passion Guy.

1889
01:15:55,788 --> 01:15:57,457
Kwang Kyu.

1890
01:15:57,458 --> 01:15:58,517
Passion Guy.

1891
01:15:58,518 --> 01:16:00,857
- Since we're talking like this...
- Yes.

1892
01:16:00,858 --> 01:16:02,888
- and Nam Jin is here too, - Yes.

1893
01:16:02,928 --> 01:16:05,858
please say the line in "Ode to My Father."

1894
01:16:06,328 --> 01:16:07,467
- Oh, right.
- What was that?

1895
01:16:07,468 --> 01:16:08,798
Do you remember the line?

1896
01:16:09,268 --> 01:16:11,597
It went like this.

1897
01:16:11,598 --> 01:16:14,467
"Gosh, I'm popular everywhere, from the front lines to the rear."

1898
01:16:14,468 --> 01:16:17,537
Oh, right.

1899
01:16:17,538 --> 01:16:19,877
- I remember now.
- You said something like this?

1900
01:16:19,878 --> 01:16:20,978
I remember.

1901
01:16:22,148 --> 01:16:24,777
Gosh, I'm popular everywhere, from the front lines to the rear.

1902
01:16:24,778 --> 01:16:25,917
(He portrayed Nam Jin perfectly.)

1903
01:16:25,918 --> 01:16:28,217
People recognized me even in Vietnam.

1904
01:16:28,218 --> 01:16:29,887
In Vietnam?

1905
01:16:29,888 --> 01:16:31,457
(He's very satisfied.)

1906
01:16:31,458 --> 01:16:32,657
Happy New Year.

1907
01:16:32,658 --> 01:16:35,758
- Okay.
- Please say the slogan.

1908
01:16:36,258 --> 01:16:37,927
Show them why we're Grumpy Secretaries.

1909
01:16:37,928 --> 01:16:39,027
(Saying it automatically)

1910
01:16:39,028 --> 01:16:40,627
Show them why I'm Lee Seo Jin.

1911
01:16:40,628 --> 01:16:42,627
Show them why I'm Kim Kwang Kyu.

1912
01:16:42,628 --> 01:16:43,697
(They shout the slogan whenever they meet the original creator.)

1913
01:16:43,698 --> 01:16:45,168
Prove them!

1914
01:16:45,238 --> 01:16:46,607
Yes, sir!

1915
01:16:46,608 --> 01:16:47,907
Are you going to show them this time?

1916
01:16:47,908 --> 01:16:49,538
- We're going to show them.
- Okay. Thank you.

1917
01:16:49,838 --> 01:16:51,308
- Bye.
- Bye.

1918
01:16:52,178 --> 01:16:53,847
He never hesitates.

1919
01:16:53,848 --> 01:16:56,247
- I feel...
- Okay.

1920
01:16:56,248 --> 01:16:58,078
a deep connection with him.

1921
01:16:58,448 --> 01:16:59,448
He seems like a friendly guy.

1922
01:16:59,449 --> 01:17:01,147
- He's loyal too. He's nice.
- Yes.

1923
01:17:01,148 --> 01:17:05,987
If I had to pick the most meaningful moment of my life,

1924
01:17:05,988 --> 01:17:09,128
-Yes.
- it'd be the Vietnam War.

1925
01:17:10,198 --> 01:17:11,558
- When I was in Marine Corps.
- I see.

1926
01:17:11,898 --> 01:17:14,298
That's what made me who I am.

1927
01:17:14,428 --> 01:17:15,668
Even to this day.

1928
01:17:16,968 --> 01:17:17,968
It's important to me.

1929
01:17:17,969 --> 01:17:19,808
Have you ever been beaten so badly that your anus tore?

1930
01:17:22,708 --> 01:17:24,177
(Glancing)

1931
01:17:24,178 --> 01:17:25,808
I have.

1932
01:17:26,508 --> 01:17:28,007
- You have?
- He had hemorrhoids.

1933
01:17:28,008 --> 01:17:30,547
- I had hemorrhoids.
- You had hemorrhoids?

1934
01:17:30,548 --> 01:17:32,277
(Secretary Kim has experienced it in a different way.)

1935
01:17:32,278 --> 01:17:33,947
It was when I was training in the army.

1936
01:17:33,948 --> 01:17:36,787
When I first went to Vietnam,

1937
01:17:36,788 --> 01:17:38,188
the other soldiers beat me harder because I'd had an easy life.

1938
01:17:39,558 --> 01:17:40,588
Well...

1939
01:17:41,058 --> 01:17:43,087
They started beating me on the very first day.

1940
01:17:43,088 --> 01:17:44,097
(Being a celebrity made his military life even harder.)

1941
01:17:44,098 --> 01:17:47,568
I couldn't even sleep because they would beat me if I did.

1942
01:17:47,898 --> 01:17:48,898
- Right.
- My backside hurt so much...

1943
01:17:48,898 --> 01:17:49,898
that I couldn't even sit.

1944
01:17:49,899 --> 01:17:52,967
In war, it doesn't matter if you're rich or an actor.

1945
01:17:52,968 --> 01:17:55,267
Education and fame mean nothing.

1946
01:17:55,268 --> 01:17:57,737
In fact, those things work against you.

1947
01:17:57,738 --> 01:17:59,608
They give others more reason to pick on you.

1948
01:17:59,908 --> 01:18:01,777
I was lucky to have good parents.

1949
01:18:01,778 --> 01:18:03,578
I grew up carefree and fearless.

1950
01:18:03,848 --> 01:18:06,217
Then I became famous, so nothing could stop me.

1951
01:18:06,218 --> 01:18:08,987
Imagine going to war at the height of your popularity.

1952
01:18:08,988 --> 01:18:10,017
(At 24, in the prime of his youth, he went to Vietnam.)

1953
01:18:10,018 --> 01:18:12,187
Imagine what it'd be like.

1954
01:18:12,188 --> 01:18:15,988
"Am I shooting a movie? Am I really in the military?"

1955
01:18:16,228 --> 01:18:18,227
It didn't feel real at night...

1956
01:18:18,228 --> 01:18:20,298
when bullets were flying back and forth.

1957
01:18:20,598 --> 01:18:23,097
We went out on night ambushes,

1958
01:18:23,098 --> 01:18:25,337
and each morning we returned, some of us were gone.

1959
01:18:25,338 --> 01:18:26,368
(Facing death every day made him appreciate life.)

1960
01:18:26,768 --> 01:18:29,307
That's the most valuable experience I have.

1961
01:18:29,308 --> 01:18:31,777
No matter what happens, when I think about those times,

1962
01:18:31,778 --> 01:18:33,947
everything seems okay, and it gives me courage to go on.

1963
01:18:33,948 --> 01:18:35,077
That's what keeps me going.

1964
01:18:35,078 --> 01:18:38,118
- You become fearless.
- Yes.

1965
01:18:38,348 --> 01:18:40,287
He didn't fight in a war,

1966
01:18:40,288 --> 01:18:43,017
but Elvis Presley joined the army during the peak of his fame.

1967
01:18:43,018 --> 01:18:46,887
- He went to Germany.
- Yes, he served in Germany.

1968
01:18:46,888 --> 01:18:47,987
He didn't go to war.

1969
01:18:47,988 --> 01:18:49,927
- During the peak of his fame.
- Right.

1970
01:18:49,928 --> 01:18:51,457
You have something...

1971
01:18:51,458 --> 01:18:52,857
- We have similar experience.
- in common.

1972
01:18:52,858 --> 01:18:55,967
Among American singers, Elvis Presley...

1973
01:18:55,968 --> 01:18:57,797
unusually starred in films.

1974
01:18:57,798 --> 01:18:59,497
He appeared in many movies.

1975
01:18:59,498 --> 01:19:01,737
- We have many things...
- Yes, you do.

1976
01:19:01,738 --> 01:19:04,508
- in common.
- Yes.

1977
01:19:05,578 --> 01:19:07,508
Do you know what he had done before he became a singer?

1978
01:19:08,348 --> 01:19:10,078
- He was a truck driver.
- Yes.

1979
01:19:10,618 --> 01:19:12,878
Seo Jin.

1980
01:19:13,588 --> 01:19:15,417
You're a celebrity indeed.

1981
01:19:15,418 --> 01:19:16,717
(I love Secretary Lee.)

1982
01:19:16,718 --> 01:19:17,987
You're a celebrity,

1983
01:19:17,988 --> 01:19:19,257
- not just an actor.
- He's...

1984
01:19:19,258 --> 01:19:20,687
like a Hollywood music commentator.

1985
01:19:20,688 --> 01:19:24,257
Not many actors have that much knowledge.

1986
01:19:24,258 --> 01:19:26,927
Just as you liked American music when you were young,

1987
01:19:26,928 --> 01:19:29,267
I loved it as well.

1988
01:19:29,268 --> 01:19:30,968
- I can tell.
- Yes.

1989
01:19:31,368 --> 01:19:35,267
In our time, The Beatles...

1990
01:19:35,268 --> 01:19:36,907
- Right.
- took the world by storm,

1991
01:19:36,908 --> 01:19:38,237
but they were also influenced...

1992
01:19:38,238 --> 01:19:40,077
- by Elvis.
- True.

1993
01:19:40,078 --> 01:19:43,277
They started out imitating his music and became the Beatles.

1994
01:19:43,278 --> 01:19:44,348
Yes.

1995
01:19:44,448 --> 01:19:46,278
I think Elvis is the best.

1996
01:19:47,588 --> 01:19:48,718
He's annoying.

1997
01:19:51,118 --> 01:19:53,117
He knows a lot of random facts.

1998
01:19:53,118 --> 01:19:54,488
When did he study?

1999
01:19:56,258 --> 01:19:57,958
I can't get along with rich kids.

2000
01:19:59,458 --> 01:20:01,727
- I love American music.
- Me too.

2001
01:20:01,728 --> 01:20:04,238
I saw you singing earlier.

2002
01:20:04,638 --> 01:20:07,038
You don't use the trot singing technique.

2003
01:20:07,368 --> 01:20:09,707
I've never done trot as I said earlier.

2004
01:20:09,708 --> 01:20:11,337
I kept telling Kwang Kyu about it too.

2005
01:20:11,338 --> 01:20:13,378
"With My Love" isn't a trot song.

2006
01:20:14,778 --> 01:20:17,778
(They were watching his performance of "With My Love.")

2007
01:20:18,578 --> 01:20:21,888
It's not a trot song.

2008
01:20:22,748 --> 01:20:24,887
It's like "Suzie Q" by Lee Ju Il.

2009
01:20:24,888 --> 01:20:26,018
It goes like...

2010
01:20:26,488 --> 01:20:27,488
(It has a blues rhythm.)

2011
01:20:27,489 --> 01:20:29,458
Yes. It goes like that.

2012
01:20:29,628 --> 01:20:31,198
Soul, blues.

2013
01:20:33,028 --> 01:20:34,527
It's soul.

2014
01:20:34,528 --> 01:20:35,927
- It's soul.
- It's soul music.

2015
01:20:35,928 --> 01:20:37,998
It has a soul rhythm.

2016
01:20:38,068 --> 01:20:41,008
This is trot.

2017
01:20:41,068 --> 01:20:42,907
(Tapping)

2018
01:20:42,908 --> 01:20:44,607
This is a trot rhythm.

2019
01:20:44,608 --> 01:20:46,107
- It's "enka" in Japanese.
- "Enka."

2020
01:20:46,108 --> 01:20:47,708
This is trot.

2021
01:20:47,978 --> 01:20:50,447
Trot refers to the rhythm.

2022
01:20:50,448 --> 01:20:51,878
The rhythm.

2023
01:20:52,118 --> 01:20:55,947
Mambo, dodomba, tango, jitterbug,

2024
01:20:55,948 --> 01:20:58,588
rock and roll, jazz, and trot.

2025
01:20:59,058 --> 01:21:00,527
- It's all about rhythm.
- The word "trot..."

2026
01:21:00,528 --> 01:21:02,187
exist in English?

2027
01:21:02,188 --> 01:21:04,597
T-R-O-T. The trot rhythm...

2028
01:21:04,598 --> 01:21:05,927
originated in American music.

2029
01:21:05,928 --> 01:21:07,197
(Trot is a music genre that originated from foxtrot.)

2030
01:21:07,198 --> 01:21:09,398
Let me tell you something. Do you know Sophia Loren?

2031
01:21:09,568 --> 01:21:11,067
- I do.
- She's an Italian actor.

2032
01:21:11,068 --> 01:21:15,137
What's her most famous...

2033
01:21:15,138 --> 01:21:16,638
Italian movie?

